50|$|<b>Niaprazine</b> {{has been}} shown to metabolize to the {{compound}} pFPP in a similar manner to how trazodone and nefazodone metabolize to mCPP. It is unclear what role, if any, pFPP plays in the clinical effects of <b>niaprazine.</b> However, from animal studies it is known that pFPP, unlike <b>niaprazine,</b> does not produce sedative effects, and instead exerts a behavioral profile indicative of serotonergic activation.|$|E
